1
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,982
Mom, you be careful.

2
00:02:29,191 --> 00:02:31,235
ALPENA, MICHIGAN 1984

3
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:35,739
I think this is longer than it used to be!
What a lovely day.

4
00:02:35,948 --> 00:02:38,617
BASED ON A TRUE STORY

5
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:43,247
- Dad is looking so well.
- He is, isn't he? He always was a fighter.

6
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:49,628
- Look at Mahtob.
- She's such a daddy's girl.

7
00:02:49,837 --> 00:02:51,964
Well, so were you.

8
00:02:53,215 --> 00:02:57,511
Moody, Mahtob, Dad!
Come on. Fresh, home-made lemonade.

9
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,763
Come on, everybody.

10
00:02:59,972 --> 00:03:03,851
Mom, Daddy's teaching me
how to fish again.

11
00:03:08,355 --> 00:03:13,068
- Can I see today's catch?
- One of these days, oh ye of little faith.

12
00:03:14,236 --> 00:03:17,406
- Here you go. Dad, d'you want lemonade?
- Yes.

13
00:03:17,614 --> 00:03:18,949
OK.

14
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:21,076
- Ah.
- Sour?

15
00:03:21,285 --> 00:03:25,831
- A little.
- Not enough sugar? I never get that right.

16
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:31,170
Hey, Mahtob.
What vitamins do we get from lemons?

17
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:34,798
- What vitamins do we get from lemons?
- Vitamin C.

18
00:03:35,007 --> 00:03:37,426
Yes. What vitamins
do we get from bananas?

19
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:41,305
- Vitamin C, vitamin B and fibre.
- Right!

20
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:47,728
- None of my kids was as smart as that.
- Great. Thanks, Mom

21
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:50,439
- And what are you gonna be?
- A nurse.

22
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:53,817
- You can be a doctor as well.
- A doctor and a nurse.

23
00:03:54,026 --> 00:03:57,613
How do you teach Mahtob to fish
when you've never caught one?

24
00:03:57,821 --> 00:04:01,700
Honey, it's the best way.
This way I'm totally unprejudiced.

25
00:04:01,909 --> 00:04:06,455
He bought all this fishing equipment
and he's had her out there every day.

26
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:11,210
If it's a choice between your lemonade
and my fishing, I know where I stand.

27
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:15,339
- I wanna sit on Daddy's lap.
- Well, it's my turn.

28
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:18,967
- Don't fight over me, girls.
- You should find another lap.

29
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:27,267
And then we have... Thank you.

30
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:32,689
.. a 30-year-old woman with a Class 3
Pap smear for a TAH, so I think...

31
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:36,693
The Iranians have prayed themselves
back into the Stone Age.

32
00:04:36,902 --> 00:04:40,197
Why would anybody come to the States
to study medicine?

33
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:42,783
You can get a degree in Iran in two weeks.

34
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,493
Seven days.

35
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:48,830
The Ayatollah's got some great ideas.
A soldier gets wounded, let him die.

36
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:50,958
He's gonna go to paradise anyway.

37
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:54,711
- See that newspaper?
- The Iranian funny page?

38
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:59,800
How can he read that thing?
Looks like one of my prescriptions!

39
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:02,052
I've read that prescription.

40
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:40,465
- No, no, don't turn it off.
- It's OK.

41
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:46,847
- Honey, what's wrong?
- Nothing's wrong. I'm fine.

42
00:05:51,185 --> 00:05:54,938
What's wrong?
The family - is everything all right?

43
00:05:55,147 --> 00:05:57,191
Everybody's fine. They're fine.

44
00:05:58,275 --> 00:06:02,654
By the way, Mammal phoned.
He and Nasserine have had a baby boy.

45
00:06:03,739 --> 00:06:06,283
That's great.

46
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:12,247
A couple of doctors
were making cracks again.

47
00:06:13,749 --> 00:06:16,210
- Who were they?
- What does it matter?

48
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:19,463
It matters, Moody. It matters.

49
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:22,424
We moved here to get away from all that.

50
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:26,220
- God, it's just so awful!
- Oh, honey, forget it.

51
00:06:27,638 --> 00:06:32,643
Honey, forget it.
There are dumb people everywhere.

52
00:06:34,603 --> 00:06:36,605
Forget it.

53
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:39,566
"And the genie roared with laughter.
Ha ha ha!"

54
00:06:39,775 --> 00:06:42,361
"O thou poor thief
of a thousand alleyways. "

55
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:45,239
"You think you can marry
the Sultan's daughter

56
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:48,992
when all the princes in Persia
are seeking her hand?"

57
00:06:49,201 --> 00:06:52,246
"You foolish slave,
replied Aladdin boldly. "

58
00:06:52,454 --> 00:06:55,582
"Have you forgotten
the precious jewels in the cave?"

59
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:58,085
"You have the wits of a donkey. "

60
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:01,588
"I should put you back
into the dirty old lamp. "

61
00:07:01,797 --> 00:07:05,133
- Is there really Aladdin's cave?
- There must be.

62
00:07:05,342 --> 00:07:09,471
- Can we find it?
- I'm not sure if I know where it is, but...

63
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:13,684
You know, I was born in Persia.
They call it Iran now.

64
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:18,397
If I took you there,
maybe we could look for it together.

65
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:24,528
Iran's got caves and mountains
and deserts, just like in the story.

66
00:07:24,736 --> 00:07:28,991
And mosques
that are so beautiful they're like jewels.

67
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:33,120
When the sun shines on them
they dazzle your eyes.

68
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:35,372
Would you like to see those?

69
00:07:36,748 --> 00:07:38,792
OK. Where were we?

70
00:07:40,419 --> 00:07:42,462
- Daddy?
- Uh-huh?

71
00:07:42,671 --> 00:07:45,215
Do I hate Americans?

72
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,093
Of course not.

73
00:07:48,302 --> 00:07:52,306
Lucille says I hate Americans
because you're from Iran.

74
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:06,653
Sweetheart... Lucille doesn't really know
what she's talking about.

75
00:08:08,113 --> 00:08:11,950
So we shouldn't pay
too much attention to her.

76
00:08:12,159 --> 00:08:14,995
I've lived in America for 20 years.

77
00:08:15,204 --> 00:08:17,956
I'm as American as apple pie.

78
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:23,128
And so are you. Give me a kiss.

79
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:26,840
Big hugs.

80
00:08:27,966 --> 00:08:30,093
Mmm. Big hugs.

81
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:09,758
That was Ameh Bozorg.
It's always the same.

82
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:14,429
She cries and cries on the phone.

83
00:09:15,514 --> 00:09:20,018
"You're like a son to me.
When your mother died, I raised you. "

84
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:22,813
"I'm sick.
You're not here to look after me. "

85
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:25,482
- Is she sick?
- No, no, she's not sick.

86
00:09:26,692 --> 00:09:30,487
She's 58. She feels old, but she's not sick.

87
00:09:30,696 --> 00:09:34,074
- Same old guilt trip.
- Oh, honey, come on.

88
00:09:34,283 --> 00:09:37,160
She's your sister. Phone her more often.

89
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:40,080
Phoning's no good. She wants to see me.

90
00:09:40,289 --> 00:09:44,710
Now Mammal and Nasserine have had
the baby, everybody's there except me.

91
00:09:44,918 --> 00:09:48,630
It's been ten years.
I haven't seen my family for ten years.

92
00:09:48,839 --> 00:09:52,509
Mammal and Reza have been here.
Why doesn't she come?

93
00:09:52,718 --> 00:09:56,555
She's hardly been out of Tehran.
She wants to see me over there.

94
00:09:56,763 --> 00:10:01,727
They want to see us.
They've never met you or Mahtob.

95
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:06,148
- She asks why we can't go for a vacation.
- You'll have to explain it to them.

96
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:10,485
- Explain what?
- We can't go to Iran.

97
00:10:10,694 --> 00:10:12,696
Why not?

98
00:10:12,905 --> 00:10:16,200
I'm not taking Mahtob to Iran.
It's much too violent.

99
00:10:16,408 --> 00:10:19,536
We're not going to go sightseeing
to the Persian Gulf.

100
00:10:19,745 --> 00:10:22,915
We're going to spend two weeks
with my family.

101
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:25,709
Moody, there's too much
going on over there.

102
00:10:25,918 --> 00:10:30,047
Look, your family is welcome here
any time. You know that.

103
00:10:31,173 --> 00:10:34,218
Maybe you should just go there yourself.

104
00:10:34,426 --> 00:10:38,138
No. I don't mean that either.
None of us should go. It's not safe.

105
00:10:38,347 --> 00:10:40,682
- Mommy!
- I'm coming!

106
00:10:40,891 --> 00:10:43,018
You're getting it out of proportion.

107
00:10:43,227 --> 00:10:46,897
I haven't seen any of them for ten years.

108
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:48,524
- Honey, I...
- Mommy!

109
00:10:48,732 --> 00:10:51,318
All right! I'm coming!

110
00:10:53,862 --> 00:10:55,906
No, it's OK. Go ahead.

111
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:32,484
Honey, I want to go more than anything.

112
00:11:32,693 --> 00:11:35,529
I miss them so much.

113
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:38,824
You're always talking
about how important family is.

114
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:44,371
All I want to do is go for two weeks
with you and Mahtob and visit my family.

115
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:48,250
- Moody, it scares me.
- What scares you, honey?

116
00:11:49,334 --> 00:11:51,920
Look at me.

117
00:11:52,129 --> 00:11:57,676
Do you honestly think that I would take
you and Mahtob anywhere dangerous?

118
00:11:59,011 --> 00:12:02,306
I love you both
more than anything in the whole world.

119
00:12:02,514 --> 00:12:06,059
Listen. Mahtob's got a vacation.

120
00:12:06,268 --> 00:12:09,813
She starts a new school. It's a good time.

121
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,577
I swear to you...

122
00:12:24,912 --> 00:12:27,122
on the sacred Koran

123
00:12:27,331 --> 00:12:33,378
that you won't be in any danger,
that we'll be back after two weeks

124
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:38,759
and that I wouldn't do anything
to jeopardise yours or Mahtob's safety.

125
00:12:41,512 --> 00:12:45,516
Come on, honey.
It's not such a big deal.

126
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,747
Look what they're doing.

127
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:04,178
- Hello, Betty.
- Hello, Nasserine.

128
00:14:04,386 --> 00:14:06,513
It's so good to see you.

129
00:14:10,601 --> 00:14:13,020
This is Mahtob.

130
00:14:13,228 --> 00:14:17,900
- Betty! Betty! This is Ameh Bozorg!
- Sweetheart, that's Daddy's sister.

131
00:14:20,819 --> 00:14:24,865
- Oh, my goodness. Look. Mahtob.
- Mahtob!

132
00:14:26,158 --> 00:14:28,702
Moonlight. You are moonlight.

133
00:14:28,911 --> 00:14:32,164
I know. Mahtob means "moonlight".

134
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:34,166
Mahtob.

135
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:38,253
Betty? I'm so happy.
Now you can be with us.

136
00:14:38,462 --> 00:14:41,673
Yes. It's only for two weeks
but I'm very pleased.

137
00:14:41,882 --> 00:14:44,426
I remember your house
in America very well.

138
00:14:44,635 --> 00:14:48,430
- Mammal, it's so good to see you.
- Finally you're here, Betty.

139
00:14:48,639 --> 00:14:53,018
Yes. I'm so glad we could come for a visit.
Congratulations on the baby.

140
00:14:53,227 --> 00:14:54,561
Thank you.

141
00:14:56,939 --> 00:14:58,690
- What?
- Nothing.

142
00:14:58,899 --> 00:15:05,656
She says Mahtob looks almost exact
to Moody and to Ameh Bozorg.

143
00:15:17,835 --> 00:15:21,797
- Some reception, huh?
- Oh, my gosh. It's amazing.

144
00:15:22,005 --> 00:15:25,342
- You know all these people?
- All of them.

145
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:28,554
Oh, boy. This is all my family.

146
00:15:28,762 --> 00:15:32,891
- Obviously they really missed you.
- The car's just over here.

147
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,944
Go ahead. Unwrap it. It's a gift.

148
00:15:46,154 --> 00:15:48,574
Thank you. Isn't that nice?

149
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:54,663
Oh, thank you. Thank you.

150
00:15:54,872 --> 00:15:57,124
- Go on, put it on.
- Now?

151
00:15:57,332 --> 00:16:01,461
Yeah. It's, er... They've gone
to a lot of trouble. It'll make them happy.

152
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:04,214
- All right.
- It's pretty good quality.

153
00:16:06,049 --> 00:16:08,093
Let's get in the car.

154
00:16:58,727 --> 00:17:01,730
God... it all looks so different.

155
00:17:05,734 --> 00:17:09,321
You said foreign women
don't have to wear Islamic dress.

156
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:12,449
Yeah, I know. I made a mistake.

157
00:17:13,534 --> 00:17:15,953
It's all changed.

158
00:17:16,161 --> 00:17:20,457
Anyway, it's only when you leave
the house or when you go outside.

159
00:17:20,666 --> 00:17:25,295
You saw the women. I didn't recognise
half my family. They were all covered.

160
00:17:25,504 --> 00:17:31,009
Last time only half of them wore chadors.
It's all new.

161
00:17:31,218 --> 00:17:34,513
- What would happen if I didn't wear this?
- Ameh Bozorg?

162
00:17:44,314 --> 00:17:46,358
She says you'd get arrested.

163
00:17:58,704 --> 00:18:02,291
- I have to go to the bathroom.
- Wait. We're almost there.

164
00:18:15,095 --> 00:18:16,763
Hi.

165
00:18:22,311 --> 00:18:26,064
No! They're hurting him, Mommy!
They're hurting him!

166
00:18:26,273 --> 00:18:28,442
They're hurting him, Mommy!

167
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:32,529
It's a way of saying welcome.
They give the meat to the poor.

168
00:18:32,738 --> 00:18:36,116
Honey, we have to step over it.
It's expected.

169
00:18:36,325 --> 00:18:38,785
Just hang on to me.

170
00:18:52,591 --> 00:18:54,384
Mahtob...

171
00:19:14,238 --> 00:19:19,201
It's the Friday prayer.
From Tehran University.

172
00:19:50,107 --> 00:19:52,067
Mahmood...

173
00:20:01,285 --> 00:20:03,328
Prayers.

174
00:21:09,728 --> 00:21:14,566
Don't forget we've got
to get some things for your mom and dad.

175
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:19,238
Thank you, honey. Let me do you.

176
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:25,369
All right?

177
00:21:33,085 --> 00:21:37,130
<i>Fix your scarf!
Fix your hair! Cover your hair!</i>

178
00:21:58,944 --> 00:22:02,865
They didn't know you were foreign.
They wouldn't have been so harsh.

179
00:22:03,073 --> 00:22:07,619
- It was a little bit of hair.
- You gotta be careful. They're very strict.

180
00:22:08,704 --> 00:22:11,248
You must cover all.
You must not be careless!

181
00:22:11,456 --> 00:22:17,045
Every hair that is not covered is like a
dagger aimed at the heart of our martyrs!

182
00:22:17,254 --> 00:22:19,298
Come on.

183
00:22:19,506 --> 00:22:22,384
Just give it time, sweetheart. It's OK.

184
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:40,611
Look at these hands.

185
00:22:47,034 --> 00:22:49,203
Sshh!

186
00:23:01,381 --> 00:23:03,759
- Mom...
- Sshh!

187
00:23:14,353 --> 00:23:17,439
I guess that means we can eat.

188
00:23:39,002 --> 00:23:41,839
Come on, sit up straight.

189
00:23:54,059 --> 00:23:56,436
Is it because I didn't wear a chador?

190
00:23:56,645 --> 00:24:00,190
Honey, you misinterpreted.
She wasn't looking at you.

191
00:24:00,399 --> 00:24:03,527
You didn't see. She looked at me...

192
00:24:03,735 --> 00:24:07,322
It was the same feeling today
when the police stopped me.

193
00:24:07,531 --> 00:24:10,117
It was with such dislike.

194
00:24:11,910 --> 00:24:15,414
It just seems so primitive sometimes.

195
00:24:15,622 --> 00:24:19,710
All religious beliefs seem primitive
when they're not your own.

196
00:24:19,918 --> 00:24:22,546
But to cover them up
and hide them away?

197
00:24:22,754 --> 00:24:26,758
- Are they afraid of women's sexuality?
- No, that's not the reason.

198
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:30,429
Iranian women like to wear the chador.
It's a mark of respect.

199
00:24:30,637 --> 00:24:34,683
When the Shah tried to ban them
they had demonstrations in the streets.

200
00:24:34,892 --> 00:24:37,769
Most women wanted to bring it back.

201
00:24:41,148 --> 00:24:46,820
Sorry. I know it's a different culture.
I guess I... just don't understand it.

202
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:53,035
Why is Mammal angry at you,
and the others?

203
00:24:53,243 --> 00:24:56,538
They seem to be going at you all the time.

204
00:24:57,623 --> 00:25:00,792
My family... they're very religious.

205
00:25:01,001 --> 00:25:04,963
They're not sophisticated.
They're basically country people.

206
00:25:06,256 --> 00:25:09,051
It's all changed so much.

207
00:25:09,259 --> 00:25:13,138
It's all back to the Koran.
It's been that way since the Revolution.

208
00:25:13,347 --> 00:25:15,432
When they moved into this house,

209
00:25:15,641 --> 00:25:18,727
they got rid of all the furniture -
all of it.

210
00:25:19,770 --> 00:25:25,067
Now they see me and...
I seem so Americanised.

211
00:25:25,275 --> 00:25:27,778
And you have an American wife.

212
00:25:30,405 --> 00:25:32,825
- Yeah.
- I'm sorry.

213
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:35,786
The last thing I wanted
was to insult them...

214
00:25:35,994 --> 00:25:37,329
I know.

215
00:25:42,626 --> 00:25:46,004
Honey, it's going
to seem strange for a while,

216
00:25:46,213 --> 00:25:49,424
but, believe me, they want to love you.

217
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:52,886
They will. I promise.

218
00:25:53,095 --> 00:25:54,596
OK.

219
00:25:57,975 --> 00:25:59,810
- What?
- Nothing.

220
00:26:00,018 --> 00:26:02,896
- Nothing.
- What's so funny?

221
00:26:03,105 --> 00:26:06,233
You know they think
we make love all the time?

222
00:26:07,693 --> 00:26:09,528
- Who?
- The family.

223
00:26:09,736 --> 00:26:11,780
Why?

224
00:26:11,989 --> 00:26:15,367
After they make love
they have to take a shower.

225
00:26:15,576 --> 00:26:19,371
They can't pray unless they do.
It's considered unclean.

226
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:23,041
We're taking two or three showers a day!

227
00:26:23,250 --> 00:26:26,170
Oh, God! What, they think
we're two rabbits?

228
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:31,842
I'm not taking another shower.
You knew the whole time!

229
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:36,597
- I didn't know you were such a swinger!
- You knew that all along!

230
00:26:36,805 --> 00:26:40,434
- You were out in the hall giggling!
- Don't get mad.

231
00:27:29,191 --> 00:27:31,860
- Don't go.
- I have to.

232
00:27:33,111 --> 00:27:36,240
- Please stay.
- I can't.

233
00:27:36,448 --> 00:27:39,868
You've been getting up early
every morning. Don't go.

234
00:27:40,077 --> 00:27:43,080
What's the matter with you?
We're with my family.

235
00:27:43,288 --> 00:27:46,750
They're Sayyeds -
direct descendants of Mohammed.

236
00:27:46,959 --> 00:27:51,171
Of course, to a sophisticated American
that must seem primitive.

237
00:28:42,848 --> 00:28:46,518
- Betty?
- Oh, God, you scared me.

238
00:28:46,727 --> 00:28:48,562
I wondered where you were.

239
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:54,193
- I got the most beautiful picture.
- Light's gone. Coming in?

240
00:28:54,401 --> 00:28:55,903
Yeah.

241
00:29:08,207 --> 00:29:10,459
- Betty?
- What?

242
00:29:13,712 --> 00:29:16,924
Something happened
before we came out here.

243
00:29:17,132 --> 00:29:18,467
What?

244
00:29:18,675 --> 00:29:22,721
I didn't want to tell you about it.
We were coming out here, so...

245
00:29:22,930 --> 00:29:24,973
Moody, what happened?

246
00:29:32,356 --> 00:29:35,067
I got fired from the hospital.

247
00:29:36,151 --> 00:29:37,986
You got fired?

248
00:29:38,195 --> 00:29:41,448
It happened just before we left.

249
00:29:41,657 --> 00:29:44,034
Literally, two days.

250
00:29:49,248 --> 00:29:52,626
I can't believe it. They can't do that.

251
00:29:52,835 --> 00:29:57,714
Yes, they can. If they can find someone
who can do the job for less money.

252
00:29:57,923 --> 00:30:00,259
Oh, no.

253
00:30:00,467 --> 00:30:03,011
And who isn't an Iranian.

254
00:30:04,137 --> 00:30:07,724
Oh... Moody, I can't believe that.

255
00:30:07,933 --> 00:30:13,105
- Your work was going so well.
- You think they like Iranians in Michigan?

256
00:30:14,064 --> 00:30:19,111
It's always there... just under the surface.

257
00:30:21,947 --> 00:30:25,075
Not one of my colleagues

258
00:30:25,284 --> 00:30:27,786
has ever stood up for me
whenever there was trouble.

259
00:30:27,995 --> 00:30:29,580
Honey, that's not true.

260
00:30:29,788 --> 00:30:33,250
We're talking
about the medical profession.

261
00:30:33,458 --> 00:30:37,337
They're supposed to be
an educated group of people.

262
00:30:37,546 --> 00:30:39,590
What are we gonna do?

263
00:30:42,968 --> 00:30:47,306
Well... I'll tell you what we're gonna do.

264
00:30:47,514 --> 00:30:51,185
We're gonna go home tomorrow
and find out how this happened.

265
00:30:51,393 --> 00:30:54,313
We'll appeal. It's America. We've got laws.

266
00:30:54,521 --> 00:30:57,191
We've got friends.
You've got lots of friends.

267
00:30:57,399 --> 00:30:59,776
And this just can't happen.

268
00:31:02,112 --> 00:31:03,614
Hey!

269
00:31:04,698 --> 00:31:07,618
Stop that. Look at you
messing everything up.

270
00:31:07,826 --> 00:31:09,703
Get your own stuff together.

271
00:31:09,912 --> 00:31:13,999
- I don't think they'll let this through.
- Maybe Mammal can ship it.

272
00:31:14,208 --> 00:31:18,587
Do you wanna pack Toby Bunny
or carry him? It's gonna be hot.

273
00:31:18,795 --> 00:31:20,339
- Pack him.
- OK.

274
00:31:20,547 --> 00:31:23,926
Sit down and fold up
all those clothes you messed up.

275
00:31:24,134 --> 00:31:26,929
- Can I put them in the suitcase?
- Yes.

276
00:31:27,137 --> 00:31:30,140
Sweetheart, you haven't packed.
Do you want me to do it?

277
00:31:30,349 --> 00:31:32,267
No.

278
00:31:38,148 --> 00:31:43,445
You must take passport to the airport
three days before to get approval.

279
00:31:43,654 --> 00:31:47,616
- Approval? What approval?
- You must get stamp.

280
00:31:47,825 --> 00:31:50,828
- You cannot leave today.
- When's the next flight?

281
00:31:51,036 --> 00:31:53,080
I don't know.

282
00:31:58,752 --> 00:32:02,172
- Moody, what is this?
- I don't know.

283
00:32:02,381 --> 00:32:05,926
We'll have to wait
for the next available flight, I guess.

284
00:32:10,597 --> 00:32:13,141
How could you not
take care of the passports?

285
00:32:13,350 --> 00:32:18,772
- Didn't somebody tell you about this?
- Nobody thought about it.

286
00:32:18,981 --> 00:32:24,069
We'll go to the airport
and tell them we didn't know about it.

287
00:32:24,278 --> 00:32:28,615
Maybe they'll let us through. If not,
we'll sit and wait for the next flight.

288
00:32:28,824 --> 00:32:31,952
I don't know how to say this to you.

289
00:32:33,203 --> 00:32:36,331
We're not going back. We're staying here.

290
00:32:38,125 --> 00:32:40,210
What do you mean? How long?

291
00:32:40,419 --> 00:32:43,630
I want to get a job here. In a hospital.

292
00:32:44,715 --> 00:32:48,844
- What?
- I want us to live in Iran.

293
00:32:49,928 --> 00:32:52,890
No. No.

294
00:32:53,098 --> 00:32:56,310
- There's nothing for me in America.
- No.

295
00:32:58,187 --> 00:33:02,983
Are you crazy? We're Americans.
Your daughter's an American.

296
00:33:03,192 --> 00:33:05,652
Moody, honey,
you're upset about your job.

297
00:33:05,861 --> 00:33:08,322
I understand that. We're gonna fix it.

298
00:33:08,530 --> 00:33:10,616
- I want Mahtob to grow up here.
- No!

299
00:33:10,824 --> 00:33:14,119
- I think she should become a Muslim.
- No! No.

300
00:33:17,581 --> 00:33:19,625
You lied to me.

301
00:33:20,709 --> 00:33:24,963
You lied to me. You held the Koran
and swore nothing was gonna happen.

302
00:33:25,172 --> 00:33:28,467
- Mommy.
- You were planning this all the time.

303
00:33:28,675 --> 00:33:31,178
- Aren't we going home today?
- Yes, we are.

304
00:33:31,386 --> 00:33:35,516
- Go downstairs and say goodbye.
- All right.

305
00:33:41,146 --> 00:33:43,565
Moody, I know what's been going on.

306
00:33:43,774 --> 00:33:47,110
They've got no right.
You've got to resist it.

307
00:33:55,202 --> 00:33:59,414
I know how much you miss your family,
how guilty they make you feel.

308
00:33:59,623 --> 00:34:02,084
I know the pressure
they're putting on you.

309
00:34:02,292 --> 00:34:06,004
I promise we'll come back.
We'll spend time here.

310
00:34:06,213 --> 00:34:08,590
But we can't stay here.

311
00:34:08,799 --> 00:34:11,718
This is a backward, primitive country.

312
00:34:12,803 --> 00:34:15,389
I won't live here
or bring up my daughter here.

313
00:34:15,597 --> 00:34:19,434
How can you consider raising
Mahtob here with how they treat women?

314
00:34:19,643 --> 00:34:22,271
- I know it's the right decision.
- No.

315
00:34:22,479 --> 00:34:25,858
- For all of us. For you and for Mahtob.
- You can't mean this.

316
00:34:26,066 --> 00:34:30,529
I'm a doctor. They're desperate
for doctors. I could do a lot of good here.

317
00:34:30,737 --> 00:34:33,073
- Please...
- Besides, I'm a Muslim.

318
00:34:33,282 --> 00:34:35,534
- This is where I should be.
- Don't do this.

319
00:34:35,742 --> 00:34:39,037
I know it seems harsh,
but it's the best thing for all of us.

320
00:34:39,246 --> 00:34:43,542
- Mahtob could learn real values here.
- No! I won't stay here. You can't...

321
00:34:43,750 --> 00:34:45,836
You listen to me.

322
00:34:46,044 --> 00:34:48,130
You're in my country now.

323
00:34:48,338 --> 00:34:51,717
You're my wife. You do as I say.
You understand me?

324
00:34:53,468 --> 00:34:55,512
We're staying here.

325
00:35:28,837 --> 00:35:32,257
Mammal, would you translate for me?

326
00:35:34,927 --> 00:35:39,389
Please excuse me if I don't get my words
straight. I'm a bit shaken up.

327
00:35:42,893 --> 00:35:47,022
I wanted to talk to you to see
if you could understand my feelings.

328
00:35:51,944 --> 00:35:55,113
Moody and I have been married
for seven years.

329
00:35:55,322 --> 00:35:58,617
We have loved each other very much
and trusted each other.

330
00:35:58,826 --> 00:36:00,953
Trust was always very important.

331
00:36:03,872 --> 00:36:06,083
I didn't want to come here.

332
00:36:06,291 --> 00:36:09,545
Moody knew that.
I made it very clear to him.

333
00:36:09,753 --> 00:36:14,424
The only reason I came was to visit
with you so you could meet our daughter.

334
00:36:17,511 --> 00:36:19,680
But I was frightened.

335
00:36:20,556 --> 00:36:24,768
So Moody swore to me on the holy Koran
that nothing like this could happen.

336
00:36:28,313 --> 00:36:31,859
He held the Koran and he swore to me.

337
00:36:32,067 --> 00:36:34,111
Isn't that true, Moody?

338
00:36:34,319 --> 00:36:37,322
I had to. You wouldn't
have come with me if I hadn't.

339
00:36:40,075 --> 00:36:42,286
Baba Hajji, you're a religious man.

340
00:36:42,494 --> 00:36:45,873
How can Moody swear on the Koran
and then do this to me?

341
00:37:02,139 --> 00:37:04,349
Allah will forgive him.

342
00:37:09,563 --> 00:37:11,607
No! No!

343
00:37:11,815 --> 00:37:14,943
Ameh Bozorg, Ameh Bozorg,
please help me! Please!

344
00:37:25,537 --> 00:37:28,874
No, you can't do this. Damn you!

345
00:37:29,082 --> 00:37:34,713
Damn you! You can't keep me here!
You had this planned all along!

346
00:37:34,922 --> 00:37:37,174
Damn you!

347
00:38:11,667 --> 00:38:14,253
I'll be with you.

348
00:38:16,463 --> 00:38:18,715
I'll help you.

349
00:38:25,138 --> 00:38:27,349
You try to go to sleep.

350
00:38:33,230 --> 00:38:35,774
Where are the cheque-books
and credit cards?

351
00:38:35,983 --> 00:38:40,112
And I'll need the house keys
and the keys to the car.

352
00:38:43,740 --> 00:38:46,410
They're in the small bag, I think.

353
00:38:53,667 --> 00:38:55,002
Moody?

354
00:38:57,588 --> 00:39:01,175
- Talk to me. Please!
- There's nothing more to say.

355
00:39:02,759 --> 00:39:06,096
Oh, Moody, please. Please talk to me.

356
00:39:13,437 --> 00:39:14,771
Mahmood...

357
00:39:32,414 --> 00:39:36,293
<i>I told you to stop calling here.
No, she's not available.</i>

358
00:39:36,502 --> 00:39:40,631
She's also my wife,
which means she wants to do what I want.

359
00:39:41,924 --> 00:39:45,219
You're not helping him by doing this.

360
00:39:45,427 --> 00:39:49,723
Yes, I know and I'm very sorry,
but this isn't gonna help his illness,

361
00:39:49,932 --> 00:39:51,975
so please leave us alone.

362
00:39:52,184 --> 00:39:54,228
No, I will not discuss...

363
00:39:55,312 --> 00:40:00,192
I really don't care about that. The State
Department can do what the hell it likes!

364
00:40:19,336 --> 00:40:22,631
Betty, you've got to eat.

365
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:26,426
You can't keep this up.
You're gonna make yourself sick.

366
00:40:33,934 --> 00:40:39,147
If I thought you really wanted to stay here,
we could have such a great life.

367
00:40:46,029 --> 00:40:51,952
You know... when I first heard
the Shah was leaving Iran...

368
00:40:52,161 --> 00:40:55,706
it was just after Mahtob was born.

369
00:40:55,914 --> 00:40:59,960
I couldn't believe it. It was just amazing.

370
00:41:00,169 --> 00:41:04,339
They had everyone on the streets.
Millions of people.

371
00:41:06,717 --> 00:41:09,386
I should have been here.

372
00:41:10,429 --> 00:41:13,932
For the first time,
we could say to everyone,

373
00:41:14,141 --> 00:41:19,188
"This is our faith. This is our way of life.
This is who we are. "

374
00:41:20,939 --> 00:41:23,108
And nothing could stop us.

375
00:41:25,611 --> 00:41:28,155
You can't imagine what that was like.

376
00:41:41,543 --> 00:41:45,005
I know things have been hard for you,
but they'll get better.

377
00:41:45,214 --> 00:41:47,257
I promise you.

378
00:42:04,983 --> 00:42:08,695
- Dear Lord, hear our prayer.
- Dear Lord, hear our prayer.

379
00:42:08,904 --> 00:42:11,824
Please help us leave Iran
and get back to America.

380
00:42:12,032 --> 00:42:15,744
Please help us leave Iran
and get back to America.

381
00:42:15,953 --> 00:42:17,955
Please let nothing separate us.

382
00:42:18,163 --> 00:42:20,249
Please let nothing separate us.

383
00:42:20,457 --> 00:42:23,293
And keep us always safe in your care.

384
00:42:23,502 --> 00:42:26,129
And keep us always safe in your care.

385
00:42:26,338 --> 00:42:28,173
- Amen.
- Amen.

386
00:42:41,019 --> 00:42:42,855
<i>- Hello.
- Hello, Betty.</i>

387
00:42:43,063 --> 00:42:46,358
<i>- Mom? Oh, God!
- Don't talk. Just listen.</i>

388
00:42:46,567 --> 00:42:51,238
<i>You are to go to the 'American Interests
section of the Swiss Embassy.</i>

389
00:42:51,446 --> 00:42:54,324
<i>There is no US Embassy
in Tehran any more.</i>

390
00:42:54,533 --> 00:42:57,035
<i>It's on Khiaban Fereshteh Street.</i>

391
00:42:57,244 --> 00:43:01,039
<i>Their number is 625475.</i>

392
00:43:01,248 --> 00:43:03,917
- 625475...
- What are you doing?

393
00:43:04,126 --> 00:43:07,588
It was ringing. I answered it.

394
00:43:07,796 --> 00:43:10,090
Why do you wanna humiliate me?

395
00:43:10,299 --> 00:43:13,177
You don't touch the phone
or leave the house.

396
00:43:13,385 --> 00:43:14,887
- Do you understand?
- Yes!

397
00:43:56,845 --> 00:43:58,639
<i>Swiss Embassy.</i>

398
00:43:58,847 --> 00:44:01,016
American Interests section.

399
00:44:01,225 --> 00:44:03,602
<i>I can't hear. You'll have to talk louder.</i>

400
00:44:03,810 --> 00:44:07,189
<i>- I can't talk louder.
- I can't hear you, caller.</i>

401
00:44:08,273 --> 00:44:10,317
<i>'Are you there, caller?.</i>

402
00:44:11,693 --> 00:44:14,112
<i>'Are you there, caller?.</i>

403
00:44:14,321 --> 00:44:17,741
Please help me. I'm being held hostage.

404
00:44:17,950 --> 00:44:21,537
<i>You'll have to talk louder.
You're very faint.</i>

405
00:44:21,745 --> 00:44:24,998
I'm being held hostage. Please help me.

406
00:44:25,207 --> 00:44:27,960
<i>I'm sorry. I can't hear you, caller.</i>

407
00:44:34,883 --> 00:44:36,635
Who were you talking to?

408
00:44:36,844 --> 00:44:38,178
- When?
- On the phone.

409
00:44:38,387 --> 00:44:40,722
- No one.
- Don't lie to me!

410
00:44:40,931 --> 00:44:44,142
- Stop it, Daddy!
- It's OK. It's between Mommy and me.

411
00:44:44,351 --> 00:44:48,272
It was nothing. I tried to call Nasserine.
I got the wrong number.

412
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:52,192
What do you think?
You think you can lie to me?

413
00:44:52,401 --> 00:44:56,113
You think you can do anything
without me knowing about it?

414
00:44:56,321 --> 00:44:58,115
My family tell me everything.

415
00:44:58,323 --> 00:45:01,618
They're watching you all the time,
so don't be stupid.

416
00:45:01,827 --> 00:45:03,996
Mommy isn't stupid.

417
00:45:09,793 --> 00:45:14,548
She's gonna have to start school soon.
We'll have to get her the right clothes.

418
00:45:14,756 --> 00:45:17,968
- I don't wanna go to school.
- What school? When?

419
00:45:34,401 --> 00:45:37,779
American Interests... The Swiss Embassy.

420
00:45:37,988 --> 00:45:42,117
Khiaban Fereshteh is the name
of the street. Khiaban Fereshteh.

421
00:46:06,391 --> 00:46:08,435
<i>Swiss Embassy.</i>

422
00:46:09,520 --> 00:46:14,107
My name is Betty Mahmoody.
I'm an American citizen.

423
00:46:14,316 --> 00:46:16,151
<i>Show your passport inside.</i>

424
00:46:28,705 --> 00:46:30,833
- Thank you.
- Passport.

425
00:46:31,041 --> 00:46:35,420
We don't have our passports. My husband
has them. We're American citizens.

426
00:46:37,881 --> 00:46:40,801
- You can go.
- Mommy, we can go home!

427
00:46:51,395 --> 00:46:53,313
My name is Nicole Adjanian.

428
00:46:53,522 --> 00:46:56,191
Betty Mahmoody.
This is my daughter, Mahtob.

429
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,068
- Please sit.
- Thank you.

430
00:46:59,444 --> 00:47:01,572
We're so glad to see you.

431
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:05,784
I spoke with my mother
in the United States.

432
00:47:05,993 --> 00:47:08,662
I know the State Department is into this.

433
00:47:08,871 --> 00:47:12,124
We're just very happy to be here.
We'll sleep anywhere.

434
00:47:12,332 --> 00:47:15,460
For as long as it takes,
until you can get us out.

435
00:47:15,669 --> 00:47:19,298
What are you talking about?
You cannot stay here.

436
00:47:21,049 --> 00:47:25,387
I can't go back to my husband.
I wanna go home to the United States.

437
00:47:25,596 --> 00:47:27,931
That may be, but you are in Iran.

438
00:47:29,183 --> 00:47:32,603
- You are married to an Iranian?
- Yes.

439
00:47:32,811 --> 00:47:34,980
- Then you are an Iranian citizen.
- No.

440
00:47:35,189 --> 00:47:39,443
I'm not. I'm an American citizen
and my daughter's an American citizen.

441
00:47:39,651 --> 00:47:43,489
We were born in the United States.
We have American passports.

442
00:47:43,697 --> 00:47:47,409
I mean, we don't have them with us.
My husband has them.

443
00:47:47,618 --> 00:47:50,704
We've never changed our citizenship.

444
00:47:52,331 --> 00:47:56,793
If you marry an Iranian man, you
automatically become an Iranian citizen.

445
00:47:57,002 --> 00:47:59,796
The laws regarding women are very strict.

446
00:48:00,005 --> 00:48:03,509
You cannot travel anywhere
without written permission.

447
00:48:03,717 --> 00:48:07,930
You have no rights to the children.
They go to the man in a divorce.

448
00:48:09,932 --> 00:48:12,684
I'm sorry,
but you have to go back to your husband.

449
00:48:12,893 --> 00:48:15,646
But we'll never get out of Iran.

450
00:48:15,854 --> 00:48:19,650
We're being held hostage.
It was almost impossible to come here.

451
00:48:19,858 --> 00:48:24,696
Mrs Mahmoody, there are many American
women here in similar circumstances.

452
00:48:28,075 --> 00:48:30,953
May I ask you why you came to Iran?

453
00:48:36,792 --> 00:48:38,836
I don't know.

454
00:48:40,546 --> 00:48:42,589
I don't know.

455
00:48:44,174 --> 00:48:46,301
I was afraid to come.

456
00:48:49,763 --> 00:48:52,140
I wanted to please him.

457
00:48:52,349 --> 00:48:54,893
I trusted him.

458
00:48:55,102 --> 00:48:58,772
I was frightened
but I never thought this would happen.

459
00:48:58,981 --> 00:49:01,692
I thought of him as an American.

460
00:49:04,069 --> 00:49:07,573
He's changed. Oh, God, he's changed.

461
00:49:09,074 --> 00:49:10,951
Look, Mrs Mahmoody...

462
00:49:12,327 --> 00:49:17,833
Many came back after the Revolution
feeling guilty about being away,

463
00:49:18,041 --> 00:49:21,920
about turning their backs
on Iran and on Islam.

464
00:49:23,297 --> 00:49:28,802
Now Iran is an Islamic state and that's
a wonderful thing for many Iranians.

465
00:49:32,848 --> 00:49:35,851
Well, if there is anything I can do...

466
00:49:36,059 --> 00:49:41,106
Maybe if you need to organise
telephone calls to the US

467
00:49:41,315 --> 00:49:44,693
or if you want to write letters home,
let me know.

468
00:49:59,500 --> 00:50:03,170
So if Daddy asks,
we went for a walk and got lost.

