<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

483
00:51:46,315 --> 00:51:47,816
Hi.

484
00:51:48,025 --> 00:51:49,359
Hi.

485
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:55,782
Nasserine said you wanted to see me.

486
00:51:57,034 --> 00:51:59,620
I can't believe she's five, can you?

487
00:52:01,163 --> 00:52:02,498
No.

488
00:52:05,334 --> 00:52:09,838
Thank you for today.
The doll and everything.

489
00:52:14,134 --> 00:52:15,969
I miss her.

490
00:52:22,434 --> 00:52:25,687
Seems I haven't
spent much time with her lately.

491
00:52:28,398 --> 00:52:30,067
Moody...

492
00:52:31,944 --> 00:52:34,613
I wanna make it work.

493
00:52:37,866 --> 00:52:40,786
You were such a wonderful father today.

494
00:52:40,994 --> 00:52:43,997
It brought it all back.

495
00:52:44,206 --> 00:52:47,668
Honey, I want you to be happy.
I want to make you happy.

496
00:52:49,253 --> 00:52:51,797
I need you to help me.

497
00:52:56,218 --> 00:52:57,886
Oh, Betty.

498
00:53:02,641 --> 00:53:04,768
I didn't want it to be like this.

499
00:53:06,353 --> 00:53:10,274
I love you. I never wanna hurt you.

500
00:53:11,358 --> 00:53:16,071
Oh, Moody. Moody, I need you to help me.

501
00:53:19,408 --> 00:53:21,577
We can't stay in this house.

502
00:53:21,785 --> 00:53:25,789
It's my sister's house.
She'd be insulted if we went away.

503
00:53:25,998 --> 00:53:29,251
No. She doesn't want us here.
She doesn't like me.

504
00:53:31,378 --> 00:53:33,213
We got nowhere else to go.

505
00:53:33,422 --> 00:53:35,799
We could stay
with Mammal and Nasserine.

506
00:53:36,008 --> 00:53:38,468
We helped them
when they were in the States.

507
00:53:38,677 --> 00:53:42,723
Nasserine goes to classes.
I could babysit. I could help.

508
00:53:42,931 --> 00:53:44,433
Please.

509
00:53:47,269 --> 00:53:48,896
Oh, Betty.

510
00:53:50,189 --> 00:53:52,232
I don't wanna lose you.

511
00:53:56,361 --> 00:53:59,448
I want you to tell me
anything I can ever do.

512
00:54:02,868 --> 00:54:05,078
- The kitchen?
- Kitchen.

513
00:54:07,539 --> 00:54:11,126
I'll cook for you.
I'm so grateful, Nasserine.

514
00:54:17,216 --> 00:54:19,051
Thank you so much.

515
00:54:26,600 --> 00:54:29,394
I was telling them
the same rules apply as before.

516
00:54:50,249 --> 00:54:52,292
You have to wear a chador tonight.

517
00:54:52,501 --> 00:54:53,836
Oh?

518
00:54:54,044 --> 00:54:57,047
My uncle's a mullah.
He's highly respected.

519
00:54:57,256 --> 00:55:01,260
He's a very influential man.
He's written books on Islam.

520
00:55:02,845 --> 00:55:05,931
Maybe he's gonna help me get a job.

521
00:55:10,269 --> 00:55:13,105
Betty, you are very good Iranian cook.

522
00:55:13,313 --> 00:55:16,024
- Thank you.
- You are lucky people.

523
00:55:19,361 --> 00:55:21,405
Why you wear chador?

524
00:55:24,825 --> 00:55:27,494
- I thought I had to.
- But why?

525
00:55:27,703 --> 00:55:32,499
Chador is Persian tradition.
It's not necessary to wear it inside.

526
00:55:32,708 --> 00:55:35,377
It is exaggerated with some people now.

527
00:55:37,462 --> 00:55:39,506
Mahmood told me you read Koran.

528
00:55:39,715 --> 00:55:42,426
Yes. I try.

529
00:55:42,634 --> 00:55:44,511
- I like to.
- Very good.

530
00:55:44,720 --> 00:55:48,640
- You go to Koran class?
- No.

531
00:55:50,434 --> 00:55:53,937
Mahmood must send you there.
They are in English language.

532
00:56:01,069 --> 00:56:05,240
- Would you like?
- Yes. Very much.

533
00:56:10,787 --> 00:56:14,541
The Hadiths or reports
are the collected sayings of the Prophet

534
00:56:14,750 --> 00:56:18,003
with additional commentaries
by devout and learned men.

535
00:56:18,212 --> 00:56:23,175
In our readings from the Koran, we'll
consider the Hadiths when appropriate.

536
00:56:23,383 --> 00:56:26,094
- What page are we on?
- I don't know. She just...

537
00:56:27,262 --> 00:56:30,766
- You're American.
- Yes.

538
00:56:31,934 --> 00:56:36,355
.. without there being on it an imam
guiding the people to God.

539
00:56:36,563 --> 00:56:39,149
- We lived there!
- You're kidding?

540
00:56:39,358 --> 00:56:41,652
- Chicago.
- But I lived in Michigan.

541
00:56:41,860 --> 00:56:43,237
- Where?
- Near Lancing.

542
00:56:43,445 --> 00:56:46,198
- Where?
- It's a little place. Owosso.

543
00:56:46,406 --> 00:56:50,786
I lived there for five years!
I went to grammar school there.

544
00:56:50,994 --> 00:56:54,915
- My husband had his own practice there.
- My husband's a doctor too.

545
00:56:55,123 --> 00:56:57,376
I can't believe this!

546
00:56:58,377 --> 00:57:03,924
Now I work for an English language
magazine for Islamic women.

547
00:57:04,132 --> 00:57:06,677
- Have you become Muslim?
- Mm-hm.

548
00:57:08,136 --> 00:57:13,016
- Did you convert?
- Well, I wanted to, I guess.

549
00:57:13,225 --> 00:57:17,729
My husband was happy I did.
It made things a lot better.

550
00:57:20,023 --> 00:57:21,859
Er... I gotta go.

551
00:57:22,067 --> 00:57:24,111
- Ellen, it's been...
- No, really.

552
00:57:33,245 --> 00:57:34,872
Moody.

553
00:57:35,080 --> 00:57:40,127
I just met an American woman in class.
From Owosso. Her husband's a doctor.

554
00:57:40,335 --> 00:57:42,421
- Are they here?
- They just left.

555
00:57:42,629 --> 00:57:45,007
She's invited us over. Is that all right?

556
00:57:45,215 --> 00:57:47,259
Yeah, that's fine.

557
00:57:48,844 --> 00:57:52,890
I want you to ask questions
when you're out with your daddy.

558
00:57:53,098 --> 00:57:56,977
I want you to ask him questions
about taxis and buses.

559
00:57:57,186 --> 00:57:59,688
- And how much things cost.
- OK.

560
00:57:59,897 --> 00:58:06,361
All right? Ask him questions about signs.
What the signs mean, what they say.

561
00:58:06,570 --> 00:58:08,697
- All right.
- Then you can teach me.

562
00:58:08,906 --> 00:58:11,617
Why do you wanna learn all that?

563
00:58:11,825 --> 00:58:14,161
I have to if we're gonna get out of here.

564
00:58:16,163 --> 00:58:19,124
<i>- What's that?
- His name on the sign.</i>

565
00:58:19,333 --> 00:58:23,670
- What's he sell?
- All kinds of things they sell here.

566
00:58:24,963 --> 00:58:29,384
These are pictures of people
who died in the war.

567
00:58:37,434 --> 00:58:40,270
- Why all these questions, honey?
- What's that?

568
00:58:40,479 --> 00:58:45,025
- That's the rest of the market and...
- What do they do?

569
00:58:57,788 --> 00:59:00,374
Telephone. Telephone.

570
00:59:11,802 --> 00:59:15,180
The moment the Shah left
I wanted to go back to Iran,

571
00:59:15,389 --> 00:59:17,307
but Ellen didn't want to.

572
00:59:17,516 --> 00:59:21,353
So I said, "Fine. I'll go without you. "

573
00:59:21,562 --> 00:59:23,897
So she came.

574
00:59:25,065 --> 00:59:29,111
The first year in Iran
things were very bad between us.

575
00:59:29,319 --> 00:59:32,114
She couldn't adjust. Could you, Ellen?

576
00:59:32,322 --> 00:59:35,909
It took quite a time before she understood
how to be a good wife.

577
00:59:43,917 --> 00:59:45,961
Warm, isn't it?

578
00:59:47,212 --> 00:59:48,714
Yes.

579
00:59:53,677 --> 00:59:55,721
Why did you come back?

580
00:59:56,805 --> 00:59:59,683
I mean, my God,
he let you go home to the States...

581
00:59:59,892 --> 01:00:02,186
and you came back.

582
01:00:02,394 --> 01:00:04,938
Maybe at the beginning if...

583
01:00:05,147 --> 01:00:09,109
Of course there was the custody problem
with the kids, so...

584
01:00:10,611 --> 01:00:12,654
It was tough for me.

585
01:00:12,863 --> 01:00:15,949
I had no experience.
A small American town.

586
01:00:18,702 --> 01:00:22,873
- Was he violent?
- Not in the States, never.

587
01:00:23,081 --> 01:00:25,876
You're not supposed to. It's not Islamic.

588
01:00:28,670 --> 01:00:32,549
Marriages do work out here.
They can be good.

589
01:00:34,092 --> 01:00:39,348
It's been hard for me at times,
but you've got to give it time, Betty.

590
01:00:39,556 --> 01:00:42,392
Islam has such beauty in it.

591
01:00:42,601 --> 01:00:46,063
I mean, I'm glad my kids
are growing up as Muslims.

592
01:00:49,316 --> 01:00:50,901
Ellen...

593
01:00:51,109 --> 01:00:56,156
I'm so happy we're friends. When you told
me you were from home, I was thrilled.

594
01:00:56,365 --> 01:00:58,200
It was like a miracle.

595
01:00:59,284 --> 01:01:00,786
Ellen...

596
01:01:05,165 --> 01:01:08,210
I have something I want to tell you.

597
01:01:08,418 --> 01:01:12,965
If I do, can you keep it a secret?
Not tell your husband?

598
01:01:15,133 --> 01:01:17,261
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

599
01:01:18,554 --> 01:01:21,765
Ellen, I'm sorry. Please forget I spoke.

600
01:01:24,351 --> 01:01:27,521
No, it's OK. Go ahead.

601
01:01:28,605 --> 01:01:32,442
I won't tell him. That's a promise.

602
01:01:32,651 --> 01:01:34,695
Would you take this letter for me?

603
01:01:34,903 --> 01:01:37,322
I'm trying to get back home to America.

604
01:01:37,531 --> 01:01:41,827
My family is working on it, but Moody
knows where I am every minute.

605
01:01:43,871 --> 01:01:48,750
Are you crazy? Don't you realise
what can happen? Terrible things.

606
01:01:48,959 --> 01:01:50,836
You just can't, Betty.

607
01:01:51,044 --> 01:01:53,881
If you were caught,
they could execute you.

608
01:02:02,347 --> 01:02:06,477
It's for the Embassy. Please.

609
01:02:20,657 --> 01:02:22,534
Can you believe that?

610
01:02:22,743 --> 01:02:26,914
They're desperate for doctors,
they've got casualties from the war,

611
01:02:27,122 --> 01:02:30,209
but because I trained in America,
no one will give me a job.

612
01:02:30,417 --> 01:02:32,336
<i>It's not the reason.</i>

613
01:02:35,672 --> 01:02:40,677
Hard to believe this country was getting
sophisticated before the Revolution.

614
01:02:40,886 --> 01:02:44,223
We were building chemical plants,
oil refineries,

615
01:02:44,431 --> 01:02:47,184
multi-million dollar installations.

616
01:02:47,392 --> 01:02:51,980
They're all rotting because nobody knows
how to operate them!

617
01:02:52,189 --> 01:02:54,024
It's all so primitive!

618
01:02:58,862 --> 01:03:03,575
Honey, somebody needs to go to
the market. We're out of meat and things.

619
01:03:03,784 --> 01:03:07,287
- I can't go.
- It's for tonight's dinner.

620
01:03:07,496 --> 01:03:11,750
I can't go. You'll have to wait
till Nasserine gets back.

621
01:03:11,959 --> 01:03:14,044
She's late. What'll we do tonight?

622
01:03:14,253 --> 01:03:17,548
I don't know!
Can't you go by yourself for a change?

623
01:03:18,632 --> 01:03:21,176
Yeah. I can, really.

624
01:03:21,385 --> 01:03:24,888
I know the way. It's not far.
I'll take the children.

625
01:03:33,272 --> 01:03:35,983
You give me a list of everything you need

626
01:03:36,191 --> 01:03:39,736
and I'll tell you what time
for you to be back here.

627
01:03:41,238 --> 01:03:44,491
Take the baby with you.
Mahtob can stay here with me.

628
01:04:06,680 --> 01:04:10,559
- You are American?
- Yes.

629
01:04:11,643 --> 01:04:14,146
I need dozaari for the telephone.

630
01:04:14,354 --> 01:04:18,942
I was in America many times.
New York. Amarillo, Texas.

631
01:04:21,028 --> 01:04:22,738
You want to telephone?

632
01:04:24,281 --> 01:04:26,783
Please. Come. Please.

633
01:04:36,084 --> 01:04:37,586
Thank you.

634
01:04:42,716 --> 01:04:46,261
American Interests section.
Nicole Adjanian.

635
01:04:47,346 --> 01:04:51,809
Nicole, it's Betty. Have you heard anything
from the State Department?

636
01:04:53,435 --> 01:04:55,896
No, I can't.

637
01:04:56,104 --> 01:05:00,526
Because he watches me all the time
or he has somebody watch me.

638
01:05:01,819 --> 01:05:06,323
I didn't know that.
Will they let us go if I get a divorce?

639
01:05:08,659 --> 01:05:10,118
What?

640
01:05:11,370 --> 01:05:15,541
I can't do that... I can't do that.

641
01:05:17,793 --> 01:05:22,506
I won't leave her.
Nicole... Nicole, I won't leave her!

642
01:05:24,716 --> 01:05:27,928
All right. I'll get to the Embassy if I can.

643
01:05:39,314 --> 01:05:41,567
Thank you. You're very kind.

644
01:05:41,775 --> 01:05:45,487
You can use the telephone
when you want. No problem.

645
01:05:46,780 --> 01:05:50,200
- Thank you.
- I like America very much.

646
01:05:50,409 --> 01:05:53,078
My son was with University of Texas.

647
01:05:54,454 --> 01:05:56,373
That is my son.

648
01:05:56,582 --> 01:05:58,625
He is a martyr for the war.

649
01:06:00,711 --> 01:06:05,799
My name is Hamid.
Any time for telephone, you come here.

650
01:06:09,303 --> 01:06:11,346
I'm Betty.

651
01:06:16,518 --> 01:06:20,898
- Who'll take me to school tomorrow?
- I don't know, honey.

652
01:06:21,106 --> 01:06:24,026
It'll either be me or it'll be Daddy.

653
01:06:24,234 --> 01:06:28,030
- But I want you to.
- I don't know if I can, Mahtob.

654
01:06:29,615 --> 01:06:32,075
Why can't you?

655
01:06:33,869 --> 01:06:35,370
Honey...

656
01:06:38,040 --> 01:06:42,211
I promise you I'll be there
and everything will be all right.

657
01:06:44,046 --> 01:06:45,547
OK?

658
01:06:47,841 --> 01:06:49,343
Come on.

659
01:06:50,469 --> 01:06:52,137
- Dear Lord.
- Dear Lord.

660
01:06:52,346 --> 01:06:54,014
- Hear our prayer.
- Hear our prayer.

661
01:06:54,223 --> 01:06:57,851
- We beg you to help us leave Iran.
- We beg you to help us leave Iran.

662
01:06:58,060 --> 01:07:01,939
- And get back to America.
- And get back to America.

663
01:07:05,901 --> 01:07:11,907
I'll be back this afternoon, sweetheart.
I'll be back. I'll be back, sweetheart.

664
01:07:12,115 --> 01:07:15,160
Sweetheart, I'll be back.
I'll be here, sweetheart.

665
01:07:15,369 --> 01:07:19,498
- I don't wanna go! Daddy, please!
- Don't worry, baby.

666
01:07:19,706 --> 01:07:26,088
Mommy, please! Mommy, don't leave me!
Don't leave me!

667
01:08:01,999 --> 01:08:05,627
Nasserine, take the baby. I'll get the rice.

668
01:08:14,428 --> 01:08:16,096
Hamid. I can't stay.

669
01:08:16,305 --> 01:08:19,725
You must come inside.
There is someone here.

670
01:08:25,063 --> 01:08:28,025
Miss Nassimi. She came to help you.

671
01:08:30,444 --> 01:08:32,988
Hamid told me you wished to leave Iran.

672
01:08:33,197 --> 01:08:35,532
You know it is extremely dangerous.

673
01:08:35,741 --> 01:08:37,951
I have to get back to the United States.

674
01:08:38,160 --> 01:08:41,205
- Why don't you try to get a divorce?
- No.

675
01:08:41,413 --> 01:08:45,042
If I get a divorce, my husband
will get custody of my daughter.

676
01:08:45,250 --> 01:08:48,795
If they catch you with your daughter,
they could execute you.

677
01:08:49,004 --> 01:08:51,173
- I can't leave her. I have to...
- Please.

678
01:08:52,257 --> 01:08:55,636
Wait. I think we can help you.

679
01:08:55,844 --> 01:08:58,096
My brother has helped many people here.

680
01:08:58,305 --> 01:09:02,601
I will be here Wednesday and Thursday
at this time if you can come.

681
01:09:04,228 --> 01:09:08,398
Here is my telephone number.
Memorise it, please. Don't keep it.

682
01:09:12,653 --> 01:09:14,112
Thank you.

683
01:09:18,617 --> 01:09:20,077
Betty!

684
01:09:25,499 --> 01:09:27,376
I got the rice.

685
01:09:28,752 --> 01:09:30,420
Sorry.

686
01:09:39,096 --> 01:09:41,515
What happened?

687
01:09:41,723 --> 01:09:43,767
She was crying all day again.

688
01:09:45,018 --> 01:09:47,104
I had to go pick her up.

689
01:09:47,312 --> 01:09:50,274
We can't make her do this, Moody.
She's frightened.

690
01:09:50,482 --> 01:09:55,821
I know. Tomorrow they want you
to go to school with her.

691
01:09:56,029 --> 01:09:57,364
OK.

692
01:09:58,448 --> 01:10:00,868
They want you to stay with her every day.

693
01:10:01,076 --> 01:10:04,288
Of course. Of course I'll stay with her.

694
01:10:05,372 --> 01:10:07,708
They're all devout women there.

695
01:10:09,084 --> 01:10:11,128
You'll be watched.

696
01:10:13,088 --> 01:10:14,715
OK.

697
01:10:16,383 --> 01:10:19,386
I just want Mahtob to be happy.

698
01:10:19,595 --> 01:10:22,931
I want her to have a happy childhood.
Don't you want that?

699
01:10:23,140 --> 01:10:26,602
Islam's the greatest gift
I can give my child.

700
01:12:04,491 --> 01:12:08,370
You said there'd be no danger.
Mahtob could have been killed!

701
01:12:08,579 --> 01:12:13,208
America's doing this. Who supplies the
bombs, the planes? Who's backing Iraq?

702
01:12:13,417 --> 01:12:17,546
Don't be so naive. America's responsible
for this war, no one else!

703
01:12:37,191 --> 01:12:40,194
You should not behave this way.

704
01:12:40,402 --> 01:12:42,362
I had to tell Hormoz.

705
01:12:42,571 --> 01:12:45,949
It is your duty as a wife
to tell your husband everything!

706
01:12:46,158 --> 01:12:48,202
You cannot have secrets!

707
01:13:30,702 --> 01:13:33,455
Very nice. Very nice.

708
01:13:41,213 --> 01:13:44,967
Mahtob... very nice.

709
01:13:45,175 --> 01:13:46,885
Very nice.

710
01:13:50,097 --> 01:13:55,310
I am very sorry... It's bad in Iran.

711
01:13:55,519 --> 01:13:58,147
Bad for you... your husband.

712
01:13:59,314 --> 01:14:01,150
I'm sorry.

713
01:14:03,110 --> 01:14:07,281
We help you. We help you. Help you.

714
01:14:09,283 --> 01:14:12,744
- Could I use the telephone?
- Telephone? Nah! Nah.

715
01:14:16,248 --> 01:14:22,296
Husband, no telephone.
You inside. You inside.

716
01:14:22,504 --> 01:14:24,006
Right.

717
01:14:26,008 --> 01:14:30,762
You come after morning. Eleven.

718
01:14:30,971 --> 01:14:34,516
- After morning.
- I can come late with Mahtob?

719
01:14:39,980 --> 01:14:42,524
Thank you.

720
01:14:43,775 --> 01:14:46,737
<i>There are three principal ways
out of Iran.</i>

721
01:14:47,821 --> 01:14:52,201
You could go to Baluchistan and then
across the mountains into Pakistan.

722
01:14:52,409 --> 01:14:57,039
In the south-west to Bandar Abbas,
then across the Gulf by boat to Oman.

723
01:14:57,247 --> 01:14:59,291
This is the most dangerous route.

724
01:14:59,500 --> 01:15:04,505
From Tehran, across the Zagros
Mountains, through Kurdistan into Turkey.

725
01:15:04,713 --> 01:15:08,008
There are checkpoints
and the border's heavily armed.

726
01:15:08,217 --> 01:15:11,553
- Which way do you think is best?
- The Gulf.

727
01:15:14,556 --> 01:15:16,391
How much will it cost?

728
01:15:16,600 --> 01:15:21,939
When you and your daughter are back in
America, perhaps you will reimburse me.

729
01:15:22,147 --> 01:15:26,318
Dollars would be of more help to me
than Iranian currency.

730
01:15:28,654 --> 01:15:30,697
Keep in touch with my sister.

731
01:15:30,906 --> 01:15:32,908
Right.

732
01:15:37,746 --> 01:15:40,040
<i>Run! Run!</i>

733
01:15:44,962 --> 01:15:47,714
- Where were you?
- Stop it, Daddy!

734
01:15:47,923 --> 01:15:49,925
Where have you been?!

735
01:16:00,644 --> 01:16:02,604
Mommy!

736
01:16:02,813 --> 01:16:05,983
- Mommy!
- Get up! Get up!

737
01:16:16,577 --> 01:16:20,080
I'm gonna kill you! I'm gonna cut you up!
You're gonna be dead!

738
01:16:25,169 --> 01:16:26,670
Get out.

739
01:16:42,561 --> 01:16:43,896
Betty!

740
01:16:48,233 --> 01:16:49,651
Betty!

741
01:17:23,936 --> 01:17:25,771
Nicole Adjanian.

742
01:17:25,979 --> 01:17:27,898
Nicole Adjanian.

743
01:17:29,650 --> 01:17:33,904
Nicole? He's gonna kill me.
He's gonna kill me.

744
01:17:34,112 --> 01:17:36,615
He said he was gonna kill me.

745
01:17:54,675 --> 01:17:57,386
She is from the Embassy.
I need to take Mahtob.

746
01:18:00,556 --> 01:18:03,183
Nah, nah! Impossible. Child goes to father.

747
01:18:03,392 --> 01:18:06,186
He's going to kill me.
I have to get my daughter.

748
01:18:06,395 --> 01:18:08,522
Madam, you wait, husband come.

749
01:18:08,730 --> 01:18:11,316
- I want my baby!
- Madam! Madam!

750
01:18:11,525 --> 01:18:14,236
I want my baby! I want my baby!

751
01:18:14,444 --> 01:18:17,364
I want my baby!

752
01:18:17,573 --> 01:18:19,992
Betty, they won't let you take her.

753
01:18:20,200 --> 01:18:23,662
The State Department want you
to go to the Iranian Foreign Minister.

754
01:18:23,871 --> 01:18:30,043
No! The State Department don't understand
the culture. They'll only make things worse!

755
01:18:30,252 --> 01:18:34,173
- You wait for your husband.
- Tell her I want my baby. I want my baby!

756
01:18:36,633 --> 01:18:40,137
I cannot. Please, please...

757
01:19:21,094 --> 01:19:23,305
Listen, honey, don't talk right now.

758
01:19:23,514 --> 01:19:27,643
Because I have to tell you you can't talk
about Hamid or the Embassy

759
01:19:27,851 --> 01:19:31,021
because if you do,
they'll never let us get away.

760
01:19:31,230 --> 01:19:34,399
Don't say anything. Do you hear me?

761
01:19:36,485 --> 01:19:39,363
Mommy, don't leave me. Don't go away.

762
01:19:39,571 --> 01:19:41,990
I promise you. I promise I won't leave you.

763
01:19:42,199 --> 01:19:44,701
Do you hear? I won't leave you.

764
01:19:53,210 --> 01:19:57,339
- Where are Mammal and Nasserine?
- You, don't ask questions.

765
01:20:00,926 --> 01:20:03,595
Is that enough for you, sweetheart?

766
01:20:11,436 --> 01:20:13,480
They've moved in with Ameh Bozorg.

767
01:20:29,037 --> 01:20:31,623
- Moody, what are you doing?
- Mommy!

768
01:20:31,832 --> 01:20:35,377
Please don't take her!
Moody! Moody! Please!

769
01:20:35,586 --> 01:20:39,214
Please don't take her!
Moody, please don't take her! Moody!

770
01:20:39,423 --> 01:20:42,092
Moody, please! Moody!

771
01:20:46,430 --> 01:20:48,807
Moody!

772
01:20:49,016 --> 01:20:51,185
Moody!

773
01:20:52,019 --> 01:20:55,606
Moody, don't take her! Don't take her!

774
01:21:00,611 --> 01:21:05,073
Does Mommy take you on adventures?
Come on, where does she take you?

775
01:21:05,282 --> 01:21:07,493
To Koran class.

776
01:21:07,701 --> 01:21:09,786
We saw some camels.

777
01:21:09,995 --> 01:21:11,497
Yeah?

778
01:21:12,789 --> 01:21:14,833
You go anywhere else?

779
01:21:17,336 --> 01:21:19,922
How come you were
late for school yesterday?

780
01:21:20,130 --> 01:21:23,133
- We got lost.
- No, you didn't! I know you didn't!

781
01:21:23,342 --> 01:21:25,594
- We did!
- Where the hell where you?!

782
01:21:28,180 --> 01:21:30,015
- Where were you?!
- We got lost!

783
01:21:30,224 --> 01:21:32,601
- Where were you?!
- We got lost!

784
01:22:17,521 --> 01:22:19,022
Moody?

785
01:22:20,691 --> 01:22:23,068
Moody, please don't leave.

786
01:22:24,611 --> 01:22:29,408
How's Mahtob? Please!
Please don't leave. Is she all right?

787
01:23:13,202 --> 01:23:16,455
Mahtob. Mahtob.

788
01:23:37,476 --> 01:23:39,353
<i>Betty?</i>

789
01:23:41,230 --> 01:23:42,773
Betty?

790
01:23:55,702 --> 01:23:58,080
Mahtob. Mahtob.

791
01:23:58,288 --> 01:24:01,625
You brought her back to me.
Thank you. Thank you.

792
01:24:03,293 --> 01:24:07,130
My baby. Thank you, Moody.

793
01:24:12,136 --> 01:24:19,434
<i>Happy birthday to you
Happy birthday to you</i>

794
01:24:19,643 --> 01:24:23,939
<i>Happy birthday, dear Mahtob</i>

795
01:24:24,148 --> 01:24:27,693
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

796
01:25:17,117 --> 01:25:20,204
- Will you be all right?
- Yes, but when will you be back?

797
01:25:20,412 --> 01:25:25,000
- I'll be back as soon as I can. Be brave.
- I will.

798
01:25:44,728 --> 01:25:46,897
We will fly you to Bandar Abbas

799
01:25:47,105 --> 01:25:50,609
and then take you by speedboat
across the Gulf.

800
01:25:55,739 --> 01:25:58,408
I'll never be able to thank you.

801
01:25:59,993 --> 01:26:02,663
Please, Betty. There's really no need.

802
01:26:05,374 --> 01:26:09,044
Just make the journey safely.

803
01:26:13,966 --> 01:26:16,885
I wish you could have seen this
in the summer.

804
01:26:18,512 --> 01:26:21,265
All the flowers have gone now, of course.

805
01:26:21,473 --> 01:26:25,102
Gardens have always
had a special place in Persia.

806
01:26:25,310 --> 01:26:27,437
Throughout our history.

807
01:26:27,646 --> 01:26:30,732
In fact, the word "paradise"
is a Persian word.

808
01:26:32,734 --> 01:26:35,320
It's hard to believe
that the idea of paradise

809
01:26:35,529 --> 01:26:38,615
will always be
intimately connected with Iran.

810
01:26:40,909 --> 01:26:46,081
Whenever I think of what's happening to
my country, I try to remember its gardens.

811
01:26:49,960 --> 01:26:53,088
You must try and phone me now
whenever you can.

812
01:26:55,048 --> 01:26:56,758
By Christmas you'll be home.

813
01:27:10,147 --> 01:27:11,815
Betty.

814
01:27:17,571 --> 01:27:20,449
Merry Christmas.

815
01:27:21,909 --> 01:27:24,077
<i>I'm sorry. The Gulf got too dangerous.</i>

816
01:27:24,286 --> 01:27:27,706
Warships are checking
all the civilian boats.

817
01:27:27,915 --> 01:27:31,627
Zahedan is safer, so I've booked
a flight for you and Mahtob

818
01:27:31,835 --> 01:27:35,380
on Wednesday 29th January,
ten days from now.

819
01:27:35,589 --> 01:27:39,676
Wednesday. Good.
Moody's at the hospital on Wednesdays.

820
01:27:39,885 --> 01:27:43,597
On the 29th, take Mahtob
to the school bus as usual.

821
01:27:43,806 --> 01:27:46,183
We will pick you both up
from the bus stop,

822
01:27:46,391 --> 01:27:49,353
take you to a safe house
until it's time to go.

823
01:27:52,064 --> 01:27:54,441
<i>Was he in pain?</i>

824
01:27:55,984 --> 01:27:57,486
Is he now?

825
01:27:59,029 --> 01:28:02,115
How much? How long has he known?

826
01:28:03,700 --> 01:28:07,371
- So he's not responding to the treatment?
- What is it?

827
01:28:09,873 --> 01:28:13,502
- And they offered that?
- What?

828
01:28:13,710 --> 01:28:16,547
Mother, would you hold on for a moment?

829
01:28:16,755 --> 01:28:21,176
It's my father. He's not doing well.
They feel they should operate and...

830
01:28:21,385 --> 01:28:26,390
Tell her you'll go to America to see him.
Tell her you're going. Go on.

831
01:28:26,598 --> 01:28:30,060
Tell her you're going to see him.
Tell her now.

832
01:28:35,941 --> 01:28:39,361
Mom? Moody says we can come home.

833
01:28:45,409 --> 01:28:49,037
- I'm sorry about your father.
- Thank you.

834
01:29:00,174 --> 01:29:02,843
Will you be able to come home with us?

835
01:29:03,051 --> 01:29:07,181
No, I can't go.
I'd lose my job at the hospital.

836
01:29:08,974 --> 01:29:13,770
- But it's all right for Mahtob to come?
- No. You'll have to go on your own.

837
01:29:18,609 --> 01:29:21,570
- I can't go without Mahtob.
- Why not?

838
01:29:21,778 --> 01:29:24,865
You'll see your father.
What's the problem?

839
01:29:27,284 --> 01:29:29,578
I won't go without her.

840
01:29:37,127 --> 01:29:39,087
Betty...

841
01:29:40,756 --> 01:29:42,883
You'll leave as soon as possible.

842
01:29:43,091 --> 01:29:46,720
You'll see your father
and liquidate all our assets in the States.

843
01:29:50,974 --> 01:29:53,644
It's my money and I want it!

844
01:29:55,562 --> 01:29:58,857
Don't do it, Betty.
You'll never see your daughter again.

845
01:29:59,066 --> 01:30:03,570
- He won't allow you back in the country.
- My father is dying.

846
01:30:03,779 --> 01:30:07,199
I don't think he'd want you to
if it meant losing your daughter.

847
01:30:07,407 --> 01:30:10,744
Why can't I go now, come back
and later try to get out?

848
01:30:10,953 --> 01:30:14,581
You can't leave Mahtob here,
not with Moody's family.

849
01:30:14,790 --> 01:30:17,584
They're from the provinces,
more fanatical than most.

850
01:30:17,793 --> 01:30:19,795
This regime encourages them.

851
01:30:20,003 --> 01:30:24,800
Some people here consider a girl
ready for marriage at nine years of age.

852
01:30:25,008 --> 01:30:27,052
Child brides are not unknown.

853
01:30:27,261 --> 01:30:30,639
If you want to be free, with Mahtob,

854
01:30:30,848 --> 01:30:34,309
you've got to leave on the 29th
as we agreed.

855
01:30:34,518 --> 01:30:39,273
But he may send me out before,
maybe tomorrow. He hasn't said.

856
01:30:49,408 --> 01:30:51,034
For the war.

857
01:30:51,243 --> 01:30:54,705
They take them younger and younger.
12 years old, some of them.

858
01:30:54,913 --> 01:30:58,250
They give them plastic keys to paradise,
made in Taiwan,

859
01:30:58,458 --> 01:31:01,628
and tell them they'll go
straight to heaven if they die.

860
01:31:01,837 --> 01:31:04,381
They use them sometimes
to clear minefields.

861
01:31:04,590 --> 01:31:07,217
They run across the field
and get blown to pieces.

862
01:31:08,927 --> 01:31:10,262
OK.

863
01:31:14,725 --> 01:31:16,852
We've only a week to go.

864
01:31:17,060 --> 01:31:22,274
He's got to get your passport validated.
He can't do it in the time. It's impossible.

865
01:31:22,483 --> 01:31:26,403
He trusts you now.
Try and do anything you can to delay him.

866
01:31:27,946 --> 01:31:31,700
- Where were you?
- Moody. I went to the market.

867
01:31:32,868 --> 01:31:37,080
I wanted to buy my father some gifts
but I couldn't find anything.

868
01:31:37,289 --> 01:31:39,333
The one day I come home early.

869
01:31:41,502 --> 01:31:45,255
I've let you go. I've given you freedom.

870
01:31:47,716 --> 01:31:50,344
OK. Listen to me.

871
01:31:50,552 --> 01:31:56,892
If you don't do as I say, I'll lock you up
and you'll never see Mahtob again.

872
01:31:57,100 --> 01:32:00,020
On the 26th
you get on that plane to America.

873
01:32:00,229 --> 01:32:03,190
You send everything back here
and then you return.

874
01:32:03,398 --> 01:32:08,195
In the meantime, do not touch the phone
or set foot out of the house. Is that clear?

875
01:32:08,403 --> 01:32:09,738
Yes.

876
01:32:11,448 --> 01:32:13,575
Moody?

877
01:32:13,784 --> 01:32:18,163
- You booked for the 26th?
- What do you mean? Of course I booked.

878
01:32:18,372 --> 01:32:20,916
You got the validation?
Remember last time?

879
01:32:21,124 --> 01:32:24,753
Zia knows people. It's all been done.

880
01:32:38,016 --> 01:32:41,979
I hope your father gets well.
I'm sorry we can't see you off tomorrow.

881
01:32:42,187 --> 01:32:45,357
Please come back to us. We love you.

882
01:32:56,618 --> 01:32:58,829
They want me to go back to the hospital.

883
01:33:09,590 --> 01:33:11,091
I gotta go.

884
01:33:45,792 --> 01:33:47,836
I have to go to the market.

885
01:33:48,045 --> 01:33:52,049
There's a few things that I need.
It'll take me about 20 minutes.

886
01:33:52,257 --> 01:33:54,968
- I'll go.
- No, no. It's all right.

887
01:33:55,177 --> 01:33:56,887
I need some fresh air.

888
01:33:57,095 --> 01:34:01,141
I'd like to buy some gifts for my father.
There's been no time.

889
01:34:14,696 --> 01:34:19,034
Honey? Mahtob,
get your scarf and your jacket.

890
01:35:05,247 --> 01:35:07,249
Houssein.

891
01:35:08,959 --> 01:35:11,295
Houssein.

892
01:35:15,716 --> 01:35:17,759
Houssein, I have her with me.

893
01:35:17,968 --> 01:35:21,972
This is the last chance I have.
We have to leave now.

894
01:35:31,982 --> 01:35:33,817
Betty. Come.

895
01:35:38,864 --> 01:35:42,743
My brother wants you
to call your husband and delay him.

896
01:35:42,951 --> 01:35:47,122
First I must call Houssein
and tell him you're safe.

897
01:35:49,708 --> 01:35:52,961
- I forgot Toby Bunny.
- What?

898
01:35:54,004 --> 01:35:56,131
I forgot Toby Bunny.

899
01:35:56,340 --> 01:36:00,260
Honey... Honey, do you want
to go home to America?

900
01:36:01,345 --> 01:36:04,139
Mahtob, stop crying.

901
01:36:04,348 --> 01:36:06,517
Stop crying.

902
01:36:07,935 --> 01:36:09,561
Listen now.

903
01:36:10,479 --> 01:36:14,107
If we go back for Toby Bunny,
we have to stay with Daddy.

904
01:36:14,316 --> 01:36:17,110
Do you want that?

905
01:36:17,319 --> 01:36:19,905
But when will I see my daddy again?

906
01:36:20,113 --> 01:36:22,324
I don't know.

907
01:36:25,786 --> 01:36:27,287
Stop crying now.

908
01:36:28,455 --> 01:36:30,541
I love you.

909
01:36:30,749 --> 01:36:33,544
I love you. You be my big, brave girl.

910
01:36:36,964 --> 01:36:38,298
All right.

911
01:36:38,507 --> 01:36:43,137
<i>- Moody, I'm not gonna get on that plane.
- Why not? What are you planning?</i>

912
01:36:43,345 --> 01:36:46,140
Nothing. I'm not planning anything.

913
01:36:46,348 --> 01:36:49,351
<i>- I'll call the police.
- Go ahead and call the police.</i>

914
01:36:49,560 --> 01:36:52,521
<i>- There are things I'd like to tell them.
- Like what?</i>

915
01:36:52,729 --> 01:36:57,401
Like I know the clinic isn't legal.
You don't have an operating permit.

916
01:36:57,609 --> 01:37:02,489
I found out. I sit there all day long.
You think I wouldn't notice?!

917
01:37:02,698 --> 01:37:05,325
<i>I'm only trying to be good to you.</i>

918
01:37:05,534 --> 01:37:08,912
<i>- Yes.
- We don't need the police.</i>

919
01:37:09,121 --> 01:37:13,542
I agree. That won't be necessary.

920
01:37:13,750 --> 01:37:18,172
<i>So we can get together
and talk about this, Betty. Betty?</i>

921
01:37:18,380 --> 01:37:20,215
I'll have to think about it.

922
01:37:20,424 --> 01:37:24,178
You'd better.
I don't believe a word you say any more.

923
01:37:26,263 --> 01:37:31,226
How could you take Mahtob away?
You're stealing my child.

924
01:37:31,435 --> 01:37:34,396
No. I'm not gonna
promise you anything, Betty.

925
01:37:34,605 --> 01:37:37,024
You're my wife. Get your ass back here!

926
01:37:39,568 --> 01:37:41,320
Hello, Betty. This is Zia.

927
01:37:41,528 --> 01:37:47,159
Zia. I want you to tell Moody
that I have a lawyer.

928
01:37:48,702 --> 01:37:50,829
Tell Moody I won't meet with him alone.

929
01:37:51,038 --> 01:37:56,835
If he wants to talk with me, I'll be there
between 11 and 12 tomorrow morning

930
01:37:57,044 --> 01:37:59,213
and six and eight tomorrow afternoon.

931
01:37:59,421 --> 01:38:01,256
You tell him that.

932
01:38:02,508 --> 01:38:07,596
We're ready. We must go. They'll
find you if you stay any longer in Tehran.

933
01:38:07,805 --> 01:38:09,598
OK. Let me get my things.

934
01:38:09,807 --> 01:38:14,061
We've had no time to organise paperwork,
so you may have difficulty in Turkey,

935
01:38:14,269 --> 01:38:16,021
but they won't send you back.

936
01:38:16,230 --> 01:38:18,774
Get to the US Embassy
when you get to Ankara.

937
01:38:18,982 --> 01:38:22,945
We'll drive you to the Zagros Mountains.
Tribesmen will take you across.

938
01:38:23,153 --> 01:38:28,033
They're Kurdish. Most are friendly.
They know how to avoid the checkpoints.

939
01:38:28,242 --> 01:38:30,619
Do not let anybody know
you're American.

940
01:38:32,120 --> 01:38:35,707
First you must be careful
of the checkpoint outside Tehran.

941
01:38:39,128 --> 01:38:40,838
Betty...

942
01:38:41,046 --> 01:38:45,175
Very soon I hope you will be strolling
again in your own garden at home.

943
01:38:45,384 --> 01:38:47,219
In America.

944
01:39:47,070 --> 01:39:48,697
Hurry.

945
01:42:34,071 --> 01:42:35,572
What?

946
01:42:43,831 --> 01:42:45,874
What are you doing?

947
